peration would pose a potential threat to china's strategic security especially if it is a closed and deep cooperation the united states and russia should make their bilateral cooperation an open regime and let china and other countries join so that improvement of us russia strategic stability is not based on the sacrifice of strategic stability with china and other countries china and the united states may also cooperate on bmd in areas of early warning and mutual launch notification the security costs of these cooperative measures are very low and the benefits would improve stability confidence and mutual trust finally bmd cooperation between the united states and its east asian allies japan and taiwan is threatening sino us strategic stability the united states could improve chinese confidence by increasing transparency about and limiting the performance of bmd systems downloads pdf+ global missile defense cooperation and china by wu riqiang modified december 2011 pdf ap35 4_wu_riqiang pdf 350.6 kb html+ go to site external http journals rienner com doi abs parent research governance organizations and security nuclear security and risk terrorism insurgency and homeland security topics missile defense china japan russia taiwan united states search cisac publications everything publications of interest us russian cooperation in missile defense is it really possible pavel podvig center for strategic and international studies 2003 pdf+ missile defense in europe dangers and opportunities vladimir dvorkin george lewis pavel podvig theodore postol independent military review 2007 html+ us russian missile defense cooperative a pavel podvig the bulletin online 2007 html+ cover piggybacking anti satellite technologies on ballistic missile defense india's hedge and demonstrate approach bharath gopalaswamy gaurav kampani the carnegie endowment for international peace 2011 html+ pdf+ support map & directions contact rss+ rss xml feeds freeman spogli institute for internationa